  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Action for Sound Policy Formulation and Increased Community Participation in Governance.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to promote the process of formulating sound policy instruments at a national level, in Nigeria.
The project will help to mobilize Communities in Kogi State to use the tools of social accountability to monitor budgetary expenditure and demand for improved service delivery. 
The two areas of intervention are as follows:

1. Supporting National level advocacy for better policy formulation and Institutional Strengthening: This would be done by supporting the National Assembly Legislative Liaison Officer to monitor proceedings at the National Assembly, initiate processes that  provide avenues for the Church to contribute to pro-poor Bills and create avenues for collaboration with Executives and other policy makers.

2. Promotion of social accountability: This would be done by mobilizing the citizens of the target communities in Kogi State, using existing Community Structures.</narrative>
  </description>
